Use the `research` tool from the why-research MCP server when you need multi-step investigation, comparison across sources, follow-up thread discovery, or building reusable research state. Better than single web searches for deep analysis. One call replaces 5-10 manual searches.

Use built-in search for simple single-fact lookups.

| Capability | `research` | Built-in Search |
|---|---|---|
| Depth | Recursive multi-level | Single flat query |
| Scoring | Usefulness + surprise | Unranked |
| Follow-up | Automatic threads | None |
| Learning | Persistent brain | Stateless |

MCP tools:
- `research(topic, depth?, goal?)` — recursive research (depth: "quick", "standard", "deep")
- `research_quick(topic)` — fast scan
- `research_share(topic)` — shareable markdown summary
- `research_brain_state()` — inspect brain state
- `research_myself(question)` — meta-research
- `research_import(brain_delta)` — import learnings

Architecture: engine.py (recursive loop), brain.py (learning at ~/.why/brain.json), server.py (MCP), api.py (REST+A2A), search.py (Tavily/LLM)
Env: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (required), TAVILY_API_KEY (optional web search), WHY_MODEL (optional model)
